The paper discusses the development of an intrusion detection system (IDS) for controller area networks (CANs) in vehicles. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also uses deep neural networks for prediction, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the challenges of reverse engineering proprietary encodings, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper focuses on the communication between electronic control units (ECUs) in vehicles, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
